# TurboAI Frontend Rules

## Stack
Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first, no tailwind.config), Zustand v5, TanStack Query v5.

## Code Style
- `@/` absolute imports only. No relative imports.
- Import order (eslint simple-import-sort): external > `@/` internal > styles.
- Prettier: double quotes, semicolons, trailing commas, 80 chars.
- No `any`. TypeScript strict mode.

## Components
- Default to Server Components. Only `'use client'` when hooks/events/browser APIs are needed.
- Push `'use client'` to leaf components. Keep layouts as Server Components.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes.

## State
- Zustand v5: `create<T>()()` double-parens. Middleware order: immer > devtools > persist.
- TanStack Query v5: `queryOptions()` factories in `src/services/`. Use `gcTime` not `cacheTime`.
- No `useEffect` for data fetching — use TanStack Query.

## Tailwind v4
- Config in `globals.css` via `@theme` blocks. No `tailwind.config` file.
- Use `cn()` for class merging. Avoid `@apply`.

## Don'ts
- No `tailwind.config.ts`. No `cacheTime`. No single-paren `create()` in Zustand.
- No `'use client'` on layouts/pages unless truly required.
